Tools and Technologies
Amazon Web Services (AWS) EC2 — Provisioned and configured a t2.micro Linux instance running Amazon Linux 2023 AMI for web hosting.

Amazon Linux 2023 AMI — Lightweight, secure, and up-to-date Linux distribution optimized for AWS environments.

Git Bash (Windows) — Used as the local terminal emulator to connect securely to the EC2 instance via SSH.

SSH (Secure Shell) — For secure remote connection and management of the EC2 instance.

Apache HTTP Server — Installed and configured as the web server to host a static website on the EC2 instance.

Bash scripting — Automated installation, configuration, and deployment tasks for Apache and website files.

Amazon VPC & Subnets — Configured networking for secure and accessible EC2 deployment within a VPC and subnet.

Security Groups — Defined inbound rules to allow HTTP (port 80) and SSH (port 22) access to the EC2 instance.

EBS (Elastic Block Store) — Attached persistent 8 GB EBS volume as the root storage for the instance.

Key Pair Authentication — Managed SSH key pairs for secure instance access.













